### Output of checks

This bug happens on GitLab.com.

### Proposal 

1) Remove inaccessible artifacts from evidence. This can be done by removing artifacts without `artifacts:paths` in [`build_artifact_entity`](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/blob/master/ee/app/serializers/evidences/build_artifact_entity.rb#L7-L9). 

2) Update the references in CI templates to reflect the above change. This is tracked in https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/228648.

https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab/-/issues/213623 aims to replace the vuex implementation with GraphQL in the Project Severity Status component. The backend changes were still not complete and in the frontend we did a workaround by using GraphQL objects that are going to be migrated somewhere else. 

Once ~backend implement their changes, we'll need to update our GraphQL query to reflect those changes.

Currently in the frontend we do:

```
# ee/app/assets/javascripts/security_dashboard/graphql/get_instance_security_dashboard_projects.query.graphql

query projectsQuery {
  instanceSecurityDashboard {
    projects {
      nodes {
        ...Project
        ...VulnerabilitySeveritiesCount
      }
    }
  }
}
```

Probably this query will need to be updated based on the backend changes.

### Implementation

- [x] updating the graphql query to get the projects from the new location
- [x] update any component work in `ee/app/assets/javascripts/security_dashboard/components/first_class_instance_security_dashboard.vue`, though if the new query gives the projects in the same format as they are now then there should be no work here
- [x] update the tests
